<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[192,1440,1329,1481]" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">
To add to the 
<taxonomicName box="[406,553,1329,1353]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lychnuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[406,553,1329,1353]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Lychnuchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
surprise, we transfer another mimic, 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1955" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1955" box="[1024,1403,1329,1353]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lychnuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pelta">
<emphasis box="[1024,1240,1329,1353]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Lychnuchus pelta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1249,1403,1329,1353]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, to 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[192,451,1361,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Molo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,252,1361,1385]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Molo</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[465,519,1361,1385]" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Hewitson, 1868" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1868" box="[616,1009,1361,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heraea">
<emphasis box="[616,812,1361,1385]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Hesperia heraea</emphasis>
Hewitson, 1868
</taxonomicName>
, considered to be a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenee, 1865" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1865" box="[334,702,1393,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mango">
<emphasis box="[334,530,1393,1416]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Hesperia mango</emphasis>
Guenée, 1865
</taxonomicName>
), because it is not in the same clade as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" box="[1162,1386,1393,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lychnuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celsus">
<emphasis box="[1162,1386,1393,1417]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Lychnuchus celsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the 
<typeStatus box="[192,245,1425,1449]" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName box="[377,524,1425,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lychnuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[377,524,1425,1449]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Lychnuchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) but instead is closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1082,1425,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Molo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mango">
<emphasis box="[931,1082,1425,1449]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Molo mango</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(COI barcode difference only 2.7%, indicating congeneric relationship). Therefore, we form the new combination 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cong &amp; Zhang &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[1164,1287,1457,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Molo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pelta">
<emphasis box="[1164,1287,1457,1481]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Molo pelta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1300,1427,1457,1481]" captionStart-0="Figure 10" captionStart-1="Figure 11" captionStart-2="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="25.[192,275,1594,1616]" captionStartId-1="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-2="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[192,1440,215,1561]" captionTargetBox-1="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-2="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@25.[192,1440,213,1561]" captionTargetId-1="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-2="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="25" captionTargetPageId-1="29" captionTargetPageId-2="31" captionText-0="Figure 10. Genomic trees of Erionotini, Carystina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-2="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677255" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677255/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="36">Fig. 10–12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
